<bug>
	<id>53320</id>
	<title>LibreOffice 3.6 will not open on OS X 10.7.5 and Mountain Lion with "unidentified developer" error - GateKeeper</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">LibreOffice 3.6.0 will not open in OS X Mountain Lion 10.8.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">A popup window appears and says "&#x201C;LibreOffice&#x201D; can&#x2019;t be opened because it is from an unidentified developer."</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">The only way to work-around that I know of is to go to system settings, Security &amp; Privacy, and allow applications downloaded from "Anywhere"
See: http://www.macworld.com/article/1165408/mountain_lion_hands_on_with_gatekeeper.html</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Expected Result:
LibreOffice 3.6 should work immediately without extra settings, just like LibreOffice 3.5 did.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
